terror /ˈtɛrə/

(terrors) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Terror is very great fear. 恐惧 

例： I shook with terror whenever I was about to fly in a plane. 我每次要坐飞机时都害怕得发抖。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Terror is violence or the threat of violence, especially when it is used for political reasons. 恐怖活动 

例： ...the war on terror. …反恐战争。 

例： The bomb attack on the capital could signal the start of a pre-election terror campaign. 对首都的炸弹袭击可能标志着选举前的恐怖活动的开始。 

3. N-COUNT A terror is something that makes you very frightened. 使人恐惧的事物 

例： As a boy, he had a real terror of facing people. 他小时候其实非常害怕见人。

